        "rich_text_KFEFt3": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Heading",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h1>Where Are Diamonds Found in India? A 2026 Guide to History, Mining, and Modern Brilliance</h1>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "follow_us_3ggfwT": {
          "type": "follow_us",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Follow Us on"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_8DL9Df": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>India was the world's original source of diamonds for over 2,000 years. While its historical mines are legendary, the modern answer to where are diamonds found in India has evolved. This guide explores India's diamond legacy, the current state of mining, and the brilliant, ethical alternative that is shaping the future of fine jewelry: lab-grown diamonds from brands like <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry\">Lucira Jewelry</a>.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bUfHBT": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "A Journey Through India's Diamond History: From Golconda to Today",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>A Journey Through India's Diamond History: From Golconda to Today</h2>",
            "custom_id": "through"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_aTeeHz": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>India's relationship with diamonds is ancient and storied. For centuries, it was the sole supplier of these precious gems to the world. The history of diamond mines in India is dominated by one legendary name: Golconda.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_JmwFBb": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Legendary Golconda Mines: Source of the World's Most Famous Gems",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>The Legendary Golconda Mines: Source of the World's Most Famous Gems</h3><p>The Golconda Sultanate, near modern-day Hyderabad, was the epicenter of the global diamond trade from the 16th to the 18th centuries. The famed Golconda diamonds were renowned for their exceptional clarity and size.</p><p>Historical Hub: Golconda was primarily a bustling market, not a single mine. Diamonds were sourced from alluvial mines spread across the Krishna and Godavari river basins.</p><p>World-Famous Gems: This region produced legendary stones like the Koh-i-Noor, the Hope Diamond, and the Daria-i-Noor, which are now parts of crown jewels and museum collections worldwide.</p><p>Legacy of Brilliance: The term 'Golconda' became synonymous with the highest quality of diamonds, a legacy that still fascinates gemologists today.</p>",
            "custom_id": "the-legendary"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_Jc4E4r": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Primary Diamondiferous Regions of India",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Primary Diamondiferous Regions of India</h2><p>Today, the landscape of Indian diamond mining is far more consolidated. While the glory of the Golconda era has passed, one region remains central to the question of where are diamonds found in India.</p>",
            "custom_id": "the-primary"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_6WCWXy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Madhya Pradesh: The Panna Diamond Mines and Majhgawan Kimberlite Pipe",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Madhya Pradesh: The Panna Diamond Mines and Majhgawan Kimberlite Pipe</h3>",
            "custom_id": "components"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_jyNGLV": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The Panna district in Madhya Pradesh is the primary location for current diamond mining operations in the country. The famous Panna diamond mines are the heart of India's contemporary diamond production.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_xii4nX": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Madhya Pradesh: Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Majhgawan Mine: This is Asia's only mechanized diamond mine, operated by the state-owned National Mineral Development Corporation (NMDC).</p><p>Primary Source: The diamonds here are extracted from a primary kimberlite pipe, a volcanic rock formation that brings diamonds to the surface from deep within the Earth's mantle.</p><p>2026 Production Status: As of 2026, the Majhgawan mine remains the principal source of legally mined diamonds in India, though its output is modest compared to global giants like Russia or Botswana.</p>",
            "custom_id": "check"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_AYhMii": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Geological Formations: How Are Indian Diamonds Formed?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Geological Formations: How Are Indian Diamonds Formed?</h2>",
            "custom_id": "geological"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_adCWyy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Understanding the geology of Indian diamonds helps explain where they are found. There are two main types of diamond deposits in the country, which tell the story of their journey from the Earth's core to a jeweler's collection.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_rQKzCe": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Exploring Kimberlite Pipes and Alluvial Deposits The geology of Indian diamonds dictates the method ",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Exploring Kimberlite Pipes and Alluvial Deposits</h3><p>The geology of Indian diamonds dictates the method of extraction.</p><ul><li>Kimberlite and Lamproite Pipes: These are primary sources. They are deep, volcanic pipes of rock that transported diamonds from the Earth's mantle to the surface billions of years ago. The Majhgawan mine in Panna is a classic example of a kimberlite pipe.<br/><br/></li><li>Alluvial Deposits: These are secondary sources. Over millennia, erosion of primary sources washed diamonds into rivers and streams. These gems were then deposited in riverbeds and floodplains. The historic Golconda diamonds were almost exclusively found in these alluvial deposits.</li></ul>",
            "custom_id": "comparison"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_KV4qqy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Modern Reality of Diamond Mining in India (2026 Update)",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Modern Reality of Diamond Mining in India (2026 Update)</h2><p>While the history is rich, the modern reality of Indian diamond mining presents significant challenges. The scale is limited, and the process raises valid concerns about sustainability and ethics, making the conversation around where are diamonds found in India more complex than ever.</p>",
            "custom_id": "the-modern"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bJVkAD": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Environmental and Ethical Paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h3>Environmental and Ethical Concerns in Natural Diamond Sourcing</h3><p>The quest for natural diamonds, including operations at the Panna diamond mines, is not without its costs. The challenges of ethical diamond sourcing in India are significant.</p><ul><li>Environmental Impact: Mining requires moving massive amounts of earth, which can lead to land degradation, deforestation, and significant water usage.<br/></li><li>Carbon Footprint: The heavy machinery and energy required for mining contribute to a substantial carbon footprint for every carat extracted.<br/></li><li>Traceability Issues: It is incredibly difficult to trace a mined diamond's journey from a specific mine to the final consumer, making it hard to guarantee a 100% conflict-free origin.<br/></li></ul><p>These challenges set the stage for a modern, superior, and more responsible alternative.</p>",
            "custom_id": ""
          }
        },
        "rich_text_ADDTPa": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Buying Guide: Smart Tips for Hallmarked Jewellery",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Buying Guide: Smart Tips for Hallmarked Jewellery</h2><p>Purchasing hallmarked jewellery requires careful attention. Here are some smart tips when buying 22 carat gold hallmark pieces:</p><ul><li>Always ask for BIS certification before purchase.</li><li>Check making charges and weight to avoid overpaying.</li><li>Compare prices across multiple jewellers for transparency.</li><li>Understand color variations: yellow, rose, or white gold.</li><li>Prefer trusted jewellers and certified online platforms.</li><li>Inspect jewellery carefully for a clear and legible 22 carat gold hallmark.</li><li>Avoid purchasing jewellery from uncertified sources or street vendors.</li></ul><p>These tips will ensure that your 22 carat gold hallmark jewellery purchase is safe, authentic, and worthwhile.</p>",
            "custom_id": "buying"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_7bxGmb": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Shift to a Brighter Future: The Rise of Lab-Grown Diamonds",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Shift to a Brighter Future: The Rise of Lab-Grown Diamonds</h2><p>The future of fine jewelry in India is not found underground. Instead, it's being cultivated in advanced laboratories. The rise of lab-grown diamond jewelry in India offers a solution that is both brilliant and conscientious, moving beyond the traditional constraints of mining.</p><h3>What Are Lab-Grown Diamonds and Why Are They the Ethical Choice?</h3><p>A lab-grown diamond is not a substitute it is a diamond. Created using cutting-edge technology that replicates the natural growing process, these gems are identical to mined diamonds in every way.</p>",
            "custom_id": "the-shift"
          }
        },
